### Document Summary

The provided document, "LEX452 Released Document No. 2," is an administrative component of a Freedom of Information (FOI) release. It includes a cover page confirming its release under the Freedom of Information Act 1982 and a subsequent page detailing a comprehensive list of redaction codes. These codes outline the various categories of information (e.g., personal details, business information, internal operations, legal professional communication, irrelevant material) that may have been withheld or obscured in the broader set of documents released in response to FOI request LEX452.

### Relevance to FOI Request LEX452

While this specific document does not contain the core communications related to Zi Chun Wang's donor disclosures, it is an integral part of the overall LEX452 FOI release package. Its relevance lies in providing context and transparency regarding any redactions applied to the substantive documents. It explains the legal and administrative grounds under which information might have been withheld from the communications between the Australian Electoral Commission (AEC) and Zi Wang concerning his 2013/2014 donor disclosure obligations, as described in the FOI request overview.

prompt:
Considering this document as part of an FOI request, summarize the document and its relevance to the FOI request in markdown format. FYI the overview of the FOI request is: FOI Request LEX452 sought documents related to Zi Chun Wang's donations for the 2013/2014 financial year. The released documents, a schedule of three communications from the Australian Electoral Commission (AEC) to Zi Wang, confirm the AEC's process of ensuring compliance with donor disclosure requirements. These communications include an initial notification to Zi Wang regarding his obligation to complete a Donor to Political Party Disclosure Return for 2013/2014, a subsequent reminder, and finally, an acknowledgement from the AEC confirming receipt of his submitted Individual Donor Return for that period, thereby fulfilling his disclosure obligation.
